{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "What was once seen as a black issue is on the way to being seen as a central problem for all Americans.", "abstract": "Brent Staples editorial asserts that multiracial cast of demonstrations over deaths of Michael Brown and Eric Garner at hands of police officers shows that what was once seen as black issue is coming to be seen as central American problem; ponders whether America's political leadership is willing to root out abusive and discriminatory policing; observes that confirmation of Loretta Lynch as United States Attorney General will provide opportunity to review federal government's role in issue.", "section_name": "Opinion", "print_page": "22", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Brent", "role": "reported", "lastname": "STAPLES", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By BRENT STAPLES", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/12/06/opinion/hope-and-anger-at-the-garner-protests.html", "lead_paragraph": "What was once seen as a black issue is on the way to being seen as a central problem for all Americans.", "headline": {"main": "Hope and Anger at the Garner Protests ", "print_headline": "Hope and Anger at the Garner Protests", "content_kicker": "Editorial", "kicker": "Today's Editorials"}, "_id": "548267a038f0d8403d9cc340", "word_count": "856", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2014/12/06/opinion/06sat1/06sat1-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2014/12/06/opinion/06sat1/06sat1-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 400, "url": "images/2014/12/06/opinion/06sat1/06sat1-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2014/12/06/opinion/06sat1/06sat1-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "400"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2014/12/06/opinion/06sat1/06sat1-thumbStandard.jpg", "legacy": {"thumbna